description.narrative: By 2021, strengthened multisectoral capacity for scaling up nutrition interventions, which contributes to Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Micronutrients, Nutrition And Emergencies, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effective and efficient management of the Education Programme.

title.narrative: By 2021, strengthened multisectoral capacity for scaling up nutrition interventions

description.narrative: The capacity of Lao PDR for scaling up nutrition interventions was enhanced through improved functioning of multisectoral coordination at central, provincial and district levels. The capacity for planning and budgeting for nutrition – including key analysis and undertaking of surveillance data to inform planning and prioritization – was enhanced. The enabling environment for nutrition was improved through endorsement of the national decree on the regulation of breast milk substitutes; capacity for scaling up nutrition interventions was strengthened through mainstreaming of nutrition interventions in the revised RNCHN strategy and development of a technical guideline for Integrated Management of Acute Malnutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
